snippet: Some Tripoli residents have begun to see themselves as part of the neighboring conflict, increasing strain between  Sunni Muslims and Alawites.
abstract: Sectarian clashes between Sunni and Alawite militias in Tripoli, Lebanon, kill at least 17 people in what could be the worst spillover of violence from civil war in neighboring Syria; some Tripoli residents have begun to see themselves as part of conflict, increasing strain between two groups.
lead_paragraph: Some Tripoli residents have begun to see themselves as part of the neighboring conflict, increasing strain between  Sunni Muslims and Alawites.
